From a distance, Mira passed by again. She saw the bridge empty, both well keepers alone.

"The tragedy isn't that they stopped trusting," she observed. "It's that they stopped trusting at the same moment—each waiting for proof the other would try first."

The singing water requires someone to move first, then second.

Not first, then first again, then silence.
